<item>
            <title>[FELIX-4560] Unsynchonized access to map can cause infinite loop in UPnP web console plugin</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FELIX-4560</link>
                <project id="12310100" key="FELIX">Felix</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;An infinite loop loop while getting/putting elements in a map can occur in ControlServlet.&lt;br/&gt;
It uses unsynchonized maps to cache UPnP devices and icons. It seems that map implementation might cause the infinite loop, if you access an element, that is concurrently being removed.&lt;br/&gt;
In order to prevent that race condition, the access to the cache must be synchronized properly.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;To reproduce the problem do:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;run upnp and upnp web console plug-in&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;restart upnp bundle&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;click a few times on &quot;Search for UPnP Devices&quot; button in web console&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;


&lt;p&gt;The problem usually occurs on slower machines.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
